'San Diego State University' ('SDSU', 'State') is a public research university
in San Diego, and is the largest and oldest higher education facility in San
Diego County. Founded in 1897 as San Diego Normal School, it is the third-oldest
university in the 23-member California State University (CSU), and is considered
the flagship campus of the entire system. http://www.10news.com/news/sdsu-named-nation-s-top-research-
university https://ali.sdsu.edu/Pages/ALI/Engine.aspx?id=563
SDSU has a student body of more than 34,000 and an alumni base of
more than 260,000. The university awards 189 types of bachelor's degrees, 91
different master's degrees, 22 types of doctoral degrees including Ed.D, Ed.S,
DPT, J.D., Au.D, Ph.D. programs in collaboration with Claremont Graduate
University, UC Davis, UC
Riverside, http://www.bio.sdsu.edu/eb/jdeb.html UCSD, and
UCSB. http://degrees.calstate.edu/degree_list/csu-degree-
programs The university also offers 26 different teaching cred-
entials. http://degrees.calstate.edu/uploads/55/64/5564d4b6ec1584227ca2d105-
4c759f0f/Credential-Programs-08212012.pdf SDSU offers more doctoral
degrees than any other campus in the California State University system.

The Carnegie Foundation has designated San Diego State University a "Research
University with high research activity," placing it among the top 200 higher
education institutions in the country conducting research. http://classific-
ations.carnegiefoundation.org/lookup_listings/index.php The university
soon expects to be classified as "Doctoral/Research-Extensive." http://www-
rohan.sdsu.edu/%7Egra/grad/research/researchmain.html Notably, pursuant to
the ''Faculty Scholarly Productivity Index'' (FSP Index) released by the
Academic Analytics organization of Stony Brook, NY, SDSU is the number one small
research university in the United States for four (4) academic years in a
row. [http://www.sdsuniverse.info/story.asp?id=61084
SDSU Receives Top Research Distinction for Second Straight Year
(SDSUniverse.com) (Nov. 26, 2007)] SDSU
sponsors the second highest number of Fulbright Scholars in the state of
California, just behind UC Berkeley. Since 2005, the university has produced
over 40 student scholars. http://www.cies2.org/s/1064/index.aspx?sid=1064&g-
id=3&pgid=6&cid=41&SearchType=SIMPLE

In 2010, the university was ranked no. 1 in the nation by the Chronicle of
Higher Education for having the most improved graduation rate. http://chronicle.com/article/Graduation-Rates-2010-
/125587/ http://newscenter.sdsu.edu/sdsu_newscenter/news.aspx?s=72663-
 Resultantly, SDSU holds the highest four-year graduation rate out of the
23 member CSU system. http://www.sacbee.com/2012/07/16/4635070/see-which-california-
colleges.html Furthermore, SDSU is ranked No. 2 in the discipline of
Mathematics, No. 1 in Speech and Hearing Sciences, No. 9 in Computational
Sciences, No. 2 in Clinical Psychology, and No. 7 in Geography overall when
compared to 375 other universities by the Chronicle of Higher Education and the
Faculty Scholarly Index. http://chronicle.com/stats/productivity/page.php?y-
ear=2007&institution=253&byinst=Go In 2010, [[The Daily Beast]] ranked
SDSU No.21 in its list of "Tech's 29 Most Powerful Colleges." SDSU's
College of Business Administration undergraduate program ranks 87th best in the
nation according to U.S. News & World Report's 2013 "Best Business Schools,"
while its graduate MBA program ranks
86th. http://libguides.mba.wfu.edu/content.php?pid=207808&sid=2103121
The university is the only CSU campus to earn this distinction. http://grad-
schools.usnews.rankingsandreviews.com/best-graduate-schools/top-business-
schools/mba-rankings/page+4

San Diego State operates on one of the cheapest tuition and fees in the country
and across the CSU. http://www.calstate.edu/budget/student-fees/fee-
rates/TuitionFeesAllCampus.pdf As a result, SDSU has been named one of the
top 50 most affordable universities in America by multiple publications and is
also considered one of the best valued universities for out-of-state students. http://www.affordablecollegesonline.org/affordable-colleges-with-
high-returns/ http://portal.kiplinger.com/tool/college/T014-S001-
kiplinger-s-best-values-in-public-colleges/index.php Furthermore, SDSU is
one of the top 10 best public colleges for the least amount of debt after graduation. http://portal.kiplinger.com/slideshow/college/T014-S001-10-
public-colleges-with-the-lowest-average-graduat/index.html

San Diego State University is a member of the American Association of State
Colleges and Universities (AASCU), the National Association of State
Universities and Land-Grant Colleges, and the Southwest Border Security
Consortium.
